==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plücker tube
<hw>Pl⟦uum⟧ck"er tube</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[So named after
<person>Julius <etsep>Pl⟦uum⟧cker</etsep></person>, a German
physicist.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A vacuum tube,
used in spectrum analysis, in which the part through which the discharge
takes place is a capillary tube, thus producing intense incandescence of
the contained gases.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Crookes tube.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluckily</ent>⟦br⟧
